cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with dialogue modeling. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a neural network model for dialogue generation. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with modeling information flow in multi-party dialogues. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a novel neural network architecture.
